Monstera deliciosa, the Swiss cheese plant or split-leaf philodendron is a species of flowering plant native to tropical forests of southern Mexico, south to Panama.
products.description: Monstera deliciosa, the Swiss cheese plant or split-leaf philodendron is a species of flowering plant native to tropical forests of southern Mexico, south to Panama. It has been introduced to many tropical areas, and has become a mildly invasive species in Hawaii, Seychelles, Ascension Island and the Society Islands

products.overview: Commonly known as the fiddle-leaf fig, this is a species of flowering plant in the mulberry and fig family Moraceae. It is native to western Africa's lowland tropical rainforest.
